Commands to install & start the Laravel 11 server:

1) In VS Code. Go to Terminal -> New Terminal
2) Type cd my-website
3) Type cp .env.example .env
4) Type composer install
5) Type php artisan key:generate
6) Type php artisan serve
7) Go to http://127.0.0.1:8000/ in browser

Right now only the home, /rooms, and /book pages have any functionality. More to be added in future :)

To stop server from running, press ctrl+c
